Member of House of Representatives for Akoko North East/North West Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo has donated 20 motorcycles to regional security network, Amotekun in Ondo State. The motorcycles were presented to the outfit through his mother, Mrs. Yinka Tunji-Ojo on Tuesday.   Abdulrazaq declares July 29 work-free for voters…     Chief Judge jails lawyer for alleged contempt     Medical foundations partner to fight infant mortality   She said this was part of the lawmaker’s commitment to assist the state to boost Ondo’s security architecture. “We will not rest until we create a structure to combat the nefarious activities of criminals across the 18 local governments, e” she said. Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo, two years ago, donated four vehicles to the police.